[2] Summaries
- Tue 2 Jul 2019. Weekly update (no. 42) on Ebola virus disease (EVD): preparedness activities in South Sudan
[WHO; Republic of South Sudan Ministry of Health, edited]
https://reliefweb.int/sites/reliefweb.int/files/resources/20190702_Weekly%20Update%20on%20Ebola%20%20Virus%20Disease%20%28EVD%29%20%20%20Preparedness_%2342.pdf

Highlights of the week
-----------------------
- A suspected Ebola virus disease (EVD) alert was reported in Yei on 25 Jun 2019. The alert was verified and discarded by the rapid response team given that it did not meet the EVD case definition.
- 75 349 screenings were conducted for EVD in 31 points of entry. Since August [2018], the cumulative number of screenings conducted for EVD is 2 391 408.
- The glove box for polymerase chain reaction (PCR) machine has been installed and tested. An expert is in the country to mentor the National Public Health Laboratory (NPHL) personnel on procedure of sample testing and quality control for the period of 2 weeks.

Ebola situation update from North Kivu of Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC)
----------------------------------
- As of 27 Jun 2019, a total of 2297confirmed cases and 1553 deaths (case fatality ratio of 67.6%) has been reported.
- Some 116 new cases and 94 deaths were reported over the period of 18 to 27 Jun 2019, indicating that the outbreak is not under control.
- Figure 1 [at the source URL] shows the Epi-curve of new EVD cases in DRC. Although the recent trend in the number of new cases each week is decreasing, this should be interpreted with caution given the high number of unknown contacts within the community.
- An Ebola case is confirmed in Ariwara town of Aru territory, Ituri province; about 70 km (43.5 mi) from the South border.

Ebola situation update from Uganda
-----------------------------
- As of 30 Jun 2019, a total of 3 confirmed cases with 100% fatality rate.
- As of 30 Jun 2019, there are 93 contacts under follow up with none developing signs and symptoms suggestive of EVD.
- Cumulatively, 1437 individuals have been vaccinated: 78 contacts, 747 contacts of contacts and 612 frontline health workers.
- Active case search and death surveillance ongoing in health facilities and communities as the district response team investigates all alerts.

--
