As cases rise, the UN and leading aid groups have triggered a "system-wide scale-up" -- the highest level of emergency response -- putting the Ebola crisis on par with Yemen, Syria, and the cyclone response in Mozambique. The declaration is designed to increase international attention, release extra funding, and improve humanitarian coordination. - Mod.LK]

